Ring, gold, from Ancient South Arabia in the Near East (Western Asiatic), dated circa 2nd century AD. The object has a thick D-shaped hoop that flares outwards at the shoulders before widening to encompass the bezel. The source text also notes a decorated, oval bezel, with incised lines used to create the particles of the hair, tied with a filet. Provenance is given as acquired 1970â€“1999.˙˙˙˙˙˙˙